  "prompt": "What are some good songs to prank my friend?",
  "response": "Okay, let's brainstorm some prank songs! The best song will depend on your friend's taste (or lack thereof!), your relationship, and the situation. Here are some ideas, categorized for different types of pranks:\n\n**The Annoying/Repetitive Songs (Good for subtle driving-them-crazy pranks):**\n\n*   **\"Never Gonna Give You Up\" - Rick Astley:** The classic Rickroll. Timeless.\n*   **\"Baby Shark\" - Pinkfong:** If you really want to get under their skin, this is a nuclear option.\n*   **\"It's a Small World\" - Disney Parks:** Relentless cheerfulness, guaranteed to irritate.\n*   **\"What's New Pussycat?\" - Tom Jones (followed by \"It's Not Unusual\" - Tom Jones):** A very specific joke referencing a meme that is very obscure.\n*   **\"The Song That Never Ends\" - Lamb Chop:** Exactly what it sounds like.\n\n**The Misleading/Unexpected Songs (Good for the \"wait, what?\" reaction):**\n\n*   **\"Tequila\" - The Champs:** Just when they expect lyrics, BAM! \"Tequila!\"\n*   **\"All Star\" - Smash Mouth:** A great song that is overplayed.\n*   **\"Hello\" - Lionel Richie:** Great song for answering their phone with.\n\n**The Super Cheesy/Guilty Pleasure Songs (Good for embarrassing them in public):**\n\n*   **\"Barbie Girl\" - Aqua:** Extra points if they vehemently deny liking it.\n*   **\"Mmmbop\" - Hanson:** Catchy, but...dated.\n*   **\"My Heart Will Go On\" - Celine Dion:** Perfect for dramatic moments.\n*   **\"Dancing Queen\" - ABBA:** Timeless, but potentially embarrassing in certain contexts.\n\n**The Context-Specific Songs (Good for when the situation lines up):**\n\n*   **\"Another One Bites the Dust\" - Queen:** Play this when they fail at something (lightheartedly, of course).\n*   **\"I Will Survive\" - Gloria Gaynor:** Play this after they have been through a tough situation.\n*   **\"Happy Birthday\" - Traditional:** A classic to troll on a day that is obviously not their birthday.\n*   **\"The Sound of Silence\" - Simon and Garfunkel:** Play this when they say something really stupid.\n\n**Prank Ideas - How to Deploy the Song:**\n\n*   **The \"Stuck Record\":** Loop a short, annoying section of the song repeatedly.\n*   **The Unsolicited DJ:** Randomly play the song in the car, at home, or during a conversation.\n*   **The Ringtone Remix:** Change their ringtone to the prank song.\n*   **The Fake Out:** Start a normal conversation, then seamlessly transition into singing the prank song.\n*   **The Playlist of Doom:** Create a playlist filled with the prank song and play it on repeat when they are around.\n*   **The Personalized Lyrics:** Change the lyrics of a song to be about your friend, highlighting their quirks or embarrassing moments.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Your Friend's Sense of Humor:** Make sure they'll find it funny and not be genuinely annoyed or hurt.\n*   **The Context:** Don't prank them in inappropriate situations (e.g., at work, during a serious conversation).\n*   **Don't Overdo It:** A short, sweet prank is often better than a long, drawn-out one.\n*   **Be Prepared to Face the Consequences:** They might retaliate!\n\nHave fun pranking, and remember to keep it lighthearted!\n",
